reviews.review_text: it's usually about the trip... gee.... it's too many years later....I forgot what I was going to say... but it was good...came up with some buds from Penn State...first time in Rochester since sometime in 82... some how we had to find the place where they started the Moosewood Cookbook. Our friend Pam worked/created there and had fed us well.  We also had a cool poster of a and called Holy Smoke..we heard they were a good local band...so we were generally just mapping Rochester.  ...made it to the show and the energy was good and it was an anniversary tour with some extra effort to play tighter than usual. the playing is sharp, quick, and crisp... we all had fun...I like this show a lot for what it is... good aud recording puts you right there...85 indoor shows had a certain "ambiance" if you listen to such things...vocal effect, reverb and bounce... perhaps the mics used made some differences too.... I rate this high. highest? ...haven't been there yet ..still trying but sometimes I forget.

Roch-cha-cha Saw many great Rochester shows in the 80's , fun, small venue. Been listening to Fall 85 shows-30 years ago! Whoa....this night was great, charging first set, killer LIG in second. 
Such awesome times, the Oade recording captures the war memorial beautifully. Listening now, great tour
Last shows here I think
- A standard, fairly well-played show, but unremarkable apart from someone admonishing the audience to clap louder during Drums :-)
